  "chapter": {
    "number": 4,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Warning against Pride"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "What causes conflicts and quarrels among you? Don’t they come from the passions at war within you?",
          {
            "noteId": 2772
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "You crave what you do not have; you kill and covet, but are unable to obtain it. You quarrel and fight. You do not have, because you do not ask."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "And when you do ask, you do not receive, because you ask with wrong motives, that you may squander it on your pleasures."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "You adulteresses!",
          {
            "noteId": 2773
          },
          "Do you not know that friendship with the world is hostility toward God? Therefore, whoever chooses to be a friend of the world renders himself",
          {
            "noteId": 2774
          },
          "an enemy of God."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          "Or do you think the Scripture says without reason that the Spirit",
          {
            "noteId": 2775
          },
          "He caused to dwell in us yearns with envy?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          "But He gives us more grace. This is why it says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“God opposes the proud,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but gives grace to the humble.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2776
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Drawing Near to God"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          "Submit yourselves, then, to God. Resist the devil, and he will flee from you."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          "Draw near to God, and He will draw near to you. Cleanse your hands, you sinners, and purify your hearts, you double-minded."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          "Grieve, mourn, and weep. Turn your laughter to mourning, and your joy to gloom."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          "Humble yourselves before the Lord, and He will exalt you."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          "Brothers, do not slander one another. Anyone who speaks against his brother or judges him speaks against the law and judges it. And if you judge the law, you are not a practitioner of the law, but a judge of it."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          "There is only one Lawgiver and Judge, the One who is able to save and destroy. But who are you to judge your neighbor?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Do Not Boast about Tomorrow"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          "Come now, you who say, “Today or tomorrow we will go to this or that city, spend a year there, carry on business, and make a profit.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          "You do not even know what will happen tomorrow! What is your life? You are a mist that appears for a little while and then vanishes."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          "Instead, you ought to say, “If the Lord is willing, we will live and do this or that.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          "As it is, you boast in your proud intentions. All such boasting is evil."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          "Anyone, then, who knows the right thing to do, yet fails to do it, is guilty of sin."
        ]
      }
    ],
